<item>
            <title>[TIKA-383] new option for TIKA CLI to get only the languages of a document</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-383</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The TIKA CLI returns all metadata of an Document, but sometimes you only need one part of the metadatas. in my case I only need the language. I wrote a small patch, wich adds the arguments -l and --language to the CLI, who filters the metadata and return only the language. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
